<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>366</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001X</addr>  <route>axt-001X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>  <title>Scott space of a dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>(D,  \sqsubseteq )</tex> be a dcpo. The <em>Scott space</em> of <tex>D</tex> is the
  topological space <tex>(D,  \sigma ( D ) )</tex> whose open sets are given by the class
  <tex>\sigma ( D )</tex> of <link href="axt-001Y.xml" type="local" title="Scott open subset of a dcpo">Scott opens</link> of <tex>D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>367</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001Y</addr>  <route>axt-001Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>  <title>Scott open subset of a dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>(D,  \sqsubseteq )</tex> be a dcpo. A subset <tex>U  \subseteq  D</tex> is called a
  <em>Scott open</em> if it satisfies the following conditions.
  <ol>    <li><tex>U</tex> is <link href="axt-001Z.xml" type="local" title="Upwards-closed subset"><b>upwards-closed</b></link>.</li>    <li>      <tex>U</tex> is <b>inaccessible by directed joins</b>, which is to say
      for any directed subset <tex>S  \subseteq  D</tex>, if <tex>( { \bigvee }^{ \uparrow } S )  \in  U</tex>      then there is some <tex>x  \in  S</tex> such that <tex>x  \in  U</tex>.
    </li>  </ol></p><p>  The definition here follows the definition at the beginning of <b>Section 2.2</b>  of <link href="michael-smyth.xml" type="local" title="Michael B. Smyth">Mike Smyth</link>'s <link href="smyth-topology.xml" type="local" title="Topology">handbook chapter on topology</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>368</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001W</addr>  <route>axt-001W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>  <title>Scott locale of a dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  The Scott locale of a dcpo <tex>D</tex> is the locale given by the frame of opens
  of the <link href="axt-001X.xml" type="local" title="Scott space of a dcpo">Scott space</link> of <tex>D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>